track.name: Fried Hockey Boogie
comments: Just listened to "Hip shape thing" from Stones' Exile on main street and they used this exact same blues riff.
Remembering Aug 1968, Newport Pop Festival, Cost Mesa.  The Heat tearin' it up...
"Go ahead, buzz a bit Henry"...Love it !!!
just hit me in the face with some great memories a bit smoke filled but amazing
Don`t forget to boogie..BOOGIE!...Gawd,hadn`t heard the long live version in awhile...how sweet was that!!!
This song makes me get up and move!!!! Everytime!!!!!! FUCKING AWESOME!!!!Dance w me Sweets!! LOL
Oh yeah baby rock on!!!!!!!!!! Happy Friday everyone!!!!!!!!

Waited a long time to hear this on last.fm
And of course last.fm didn't give me THE WHOLE VERSION.   
Son's ah bitches !  But i'll take it.

Hmmm..I checked www.magic-records.com.. They don't seem to have it anymore. Google "info on album "Canned Heat" , and click on the Wickipedia entry, check it out, and go from there. It's worth the effort, it's a great album!
If anyone's interested, the Canned Heat C.D. i mentioned in my previous post is called "Canned Heat", and it's on the Magic Records label (a French company). Try www.magic-records.com.

Nice, I remember this well! If you want to hear some good Canned Heat get ahold of the album "Canned Heat". It may have been their 1st, I'm not sure. It's brown and has stuff like Dust My Broom, Rollin' and Tumblin', and Goin Down Slow on it. Very good all the way through!
A minor gem of a blues-rock track from the hazy end of the Sixties.
